<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: 72 to 60 pin EXP 6 to Famicom Sound Out mod]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11677&amp;p=134464#p134464"><![CDATA[
The Famicom has a rather different audio circuit. The 2A03 audio goes in through one pin, and the cartridge is responsible for mixing it before sending it out the other pin. As you noticed, most cartridges just bridge those two pins to pass the 2A03 audio straight through.<br /><br />If you want to mix two sources you'll need to balance them somehow. Different cartridges do this in different ways, usually with resistors, sometimes with an additional amplifier. On the usual NES audio mod, the expansion audio gets a ~45k resistor where it combines with the 2A03 output, right? I don't know whether that would work well with the Famicom, but I'd suggest trying a potentiometer and adjust it until it sounds right to you.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Tue Sep 30, 2014 10:24 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
