<title type="html"><![CDATA[72 to 60 pin EXP 6 to Famicom Sound Out mod]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11677&amp;p=134449#p134449"><![CDATA[
Hey guys, I recently purchased a yobo 72 pin to 60 pin converter from Stone Age Gamer and I noticed it cuts out the expansion sound with my Gimmick! reproduction and my NES Everdrive N8. I used the NESdev wiki to figure out that I needed to connect NES PIN 54 to Famicom PIN 46. I noticed Famicom pins 45 and 46 were bridged, but I didn't think that would effect anything...<br /><br />I can *slightly* hear the expansion sound but the volume is much too low, to the point of barely being perceptible, vs my sound modded control deck NES which sounds vibrant and clear. I took some pictures of my awful soldering in hope that you might have some pointers for me <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />Buying a new adapter is not out of the question.. this one is kinda beat up.<br /><br />A big issue was that there's almost no room on the pin, in fact, now i'm a bit worried about plugging this cartridge converter in because I don't want it to bend my Famicom's pins.. I was very gentle pushing the cartridge converter in for the initial test and I haven't plugged it in since.<br /><br />Any help is definitely appreciated, whether a link to an adapter I can buy that already has this functionality, tips, anything.<br /><br /><a href="http://imgur.com/4sRCCSc,lrShp03,AROrK40" class="postlink">http://imgur.com/4sRCCSc,lrShp03,AROrK40</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6708">MP2E</a> — Tue Sep 30, 2014 12:56 am</p><hr />
